column10:
Depois de muito ouvir falar sobre Witcher, resolvi jogar. Não é um jogo ruim (gostaria que existisse uma recomendação neutra no Steam), porém muito decepcionante.

-Muito foco no combate e, mesmo assim, é um combate chato e repetitivo;
-Puzzles que você resolve apertando botão. Não estou exagerando, o puzzle é "resolvido" apertando botão várias vezes bem rápido e se não for rápido, aparecem mais guardas para ter mais combate repetitivo;
-Estória (sim, escrevi correto), MEHH. Espero sinceramente que o livro seja melhor do que o jogo, pois a estória do jogo é muito fraca. "Aí, perdi minhas memórias", "Perdi minha reputação", "Não conte para ninguém que o assassino do rei tem uma característica igual a minha, mesmo depois que eu já fui acusado de mata-lo". Simplesmente não me impressionou nem um pouco. Até Baldur´s Gate tem estória melhor, sendo que Baldur´s Gate é focado em personagem, em equipe, não em estória.

Apesar de tudo que eu falei, o jogo tem sim seus pontos positivos, apenas não é um jogão memorável que você vai querer conversar com seus amigos sobre ele depois que parar de jogar. Se estiver em promoção, pode valer a pena para passar o tempo.

After much heard about Witcher, I decided to play. It's not a bad game (I wish there was a neutral recommendation in Steam) but very disappointing.

-Too much focus on combat and, even then, is a boring and repetitive combat;
-Puzzles you solve by pressing button. I'm not exaggerating, the puzzle is "solved" by pressing button several times very fast and if it is not fast enough, then appear more guards to have more repetitive combat;
-Story is mehh. I sincerely hope that the book is better than the game, because the story of the game is very weak. "There, I lost my memories," "I lost my reputation," "Do not tell anyone that the king's killer has a feature like mine, even after I was already accused of killing him." the story just did not impress me at all. Even Baldur's Gate has a better story, being that Baldur's Gate is focused on character, in a team, not in storytellying.

Despite everything I said, the game has some positives, it is just not a memorable game that you will want to chat with your friends about it after you stop playing. If it is on sale, it may be worth to pass the time.

The story is really good and gameplay can be fun at times (played with Dark Mode). The main issues I have with this game are:
- Camera controls during combat (playing with Xbox controller); 
- Delays in combat caused by long and inconsistent animations;
- Linux port is trash. If you have a modern graphics card, it is actually better to run the game through Proton! Also, remember to regularly delete old save games due to memory leak issues.
- Too many graphical effects ruin the aesthetic for me. Thankfully, it is possible to disable them in the menu (not in-game).

Despite these, I still do recommend The Witcher 2. It was sometimes an infuriating experience due to combat issues I mentioned above (which were exacerbated by the difficulty I played at) but the characters and quests, in my opinion, more than made up for the combat's shortcomings.

8/10 for me.
Finished with Roche's path, will replay the game in the future. 
Since my pc is kinda crappy I played it using the Nvdia Geforce Now service, thank you nvidia!
Very different from the original witcher 1 but still an interesting game. 

PROS:
-fluid combat but hard to get into;
-signs are stronger, yrden is much better and axii too;
-chars models are very good;
-good dialog with lots of choices that change the outcome of the story dramatically ( you can replay the game to alter those decisions);
-you feel very strong late game if you have the gear;
-variety of enemies;
-Lots of weapons and good armor design;
-Only 1 quest had a bug, thank god( looking at you Skyrim).

CONS:
-I ABSOLUTELY HATE the potion system...  because you cannot drink potions mid battle, I get its purpose its to "prepare" before the fight but in this case its very very badly made. BECAUSE I had multiple times when I drank some potions to increase healing and stats boosts, then you would go to a BIG dialog scene or some scripted events that take some time and then the potions effects are COMPLETELY GONE, the timer expired WTF. 

EXAMPLE: That draugr boss fight was completely and utter bullcrap. I drank some potions before it but then those battle spirits consumed Geralt and you would play as some soldiers who died in battle, then after you would play as Geralt again but guess what? the potions effect were GONE, the potion timer depleted. I am playing against a BOSS WITH NO POTIONS ACTIVE WTF and you cannot use potions during battle nor heal, absolutely stupid mechanic;
-Some difficulty spikes, like the 1st fight with Letho, hard boss for a very small room;
-Limited storage capacity, very annoying for me.

Final thoughts:
I would give a 9/10 but those CONS are very very annoying to me, but still a very good game o its 8/10 for me.
